metadata.name: ARABIC NIGHT
metadata.description:
The Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque is one of the six largest mosques in the world.
Located in Abu Dhabi, the capital of the United Arab Emirates. It is named after Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, the founder and first president of the United Arab Emirates.
